Gnathosoma . Generally, morphology of subcapitulum, palps and chelicerae typical as for most Neoribates (Neoribates) (see for example Grishina and Vladimirova 2009 ;
Ermilov and Kaluz 2013
; Ermilov and Anichkin 2014 ). Subcapitulum longer than wide (205 x 147). Subcapitular setae setiform, slightly barbed; a (24-28) and h (32-36) thicker than m (32-36). Two pairs of adoral setae (16-20) setiform, densely bilaterally barbed. Palps (length 110) with setation 0 -2-1-3- 9(+ω). Solenidion attached to eupathidium. Chelicerae (length 221) with two barbed setae; cha (57) longer than chb (36). Traegardh's organ distinct.
